metadata.name: Pebbles
metadata.description:
Generative series in six different ranges of 30 colors each that are combined with 150 colors forming a wall. "The Pebbles" series pays tribute to these first ancestral wall constructions in dry stone without concrete to hold them together. It is an ancient technique that dates back to the Stone Age.

This series of generatives NFTs is born from the drawings presented in Milan at the Galería Patricia Armocida. They are composed of stone blocks in 6 series of 50 originals in which 30 colors per range are combined with 150 secondary range colors in infinite shapes.

http://www.nuriamora.com/serie-piedras/

The second Range is Red.

Previous Series:
Serie 1 Blue: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/pebbles

Coded in P5js.

Source code based on Roni Kaufman previous work and used under a collaborative agreement.

Saw a dawn, and then a beam,

Each generative token has a random selection of objects, variable shadow color, camera speed and object rotation.
Created using THREE.js (2022)

metadata.name: Hidden Hash
metadata.description:
A game based around your fxhash! Hidden within all the noise are the characters to build your hash, can you find all of them?

It is HIGHTLY recommended to play this game in the largest window possible.


How to play:
If you think you've spotted a hash character then click on it! HINT! they're all grey :)
As soon as you make your first attempt, the timer begins! How fast can you find them all?
Keep track of your progress using the hash key at the top, red characters still need to be found
You can turn off the music and / or sound effects using the buttons in the top right


Good luck and have fun!

photographed in otago, aotearoa (new zealand)
metadata.childrenDescription:
generative photography project; chance of minting a double or triple exposure.

-

if you want to decode which images are captured inside your exposure can be found by using the following translations of numbers into Te Reo Māori*

one   | 1 | tahi
two   | 2 | rua
three | 3 | toru
four  | 4 | wha
five  | 5 | rima

ex. 
traits one + tahi = double exposure of one
traits one + ruatoru = triple exposure of one, two, and three

-

photographed in otago, aotearoa

*Te Reo is Aotearoa's indigenous language. unfortunately most of us only speak english.

metadata.name: Goodnight FX Beta
metadata.description:
To commemorate the end of one chapter and beginning of the next. 

Thank you fxhash and everyone involved for giving us all a space to grow. 
Due to health issues, I have been unable to work since 2018 and can not begin to describe how grateful I am for this space. I'm learning more and more everyday and can't wait to use showcase my new skills when the update releases. 

Each generation consists of landscape, moon, stars, fog, and light pollution totaling 6,480 possible variations. 

Made using purespider template, original photos, lightroom, and procreate. 

Landscapes are from 10 different locations around the world.
Original moon pic shot with Nikon D7200.

Anyone who mints more than one will receive next project, "Northern Lights" for free. 
Preview on twitter @munchie_maker

Special thanks to purespider, scoopta, ciphrd, nuduru, and everyone else who helped me figure out how to get started. 

Can't wait to see what the future holds, see you all on the other side!!

metadata.name: The Valley • Landscape study
metadata.description:
Code-generated landscapes inspired by the valley I live in.

This study focuses on building harmonious color palettes, grainy textures and bringing back the feeling of contemplating vast landscapes. Textures are inspired by vintage travel posters from early 20th century.

Main features :
- Random aspect ratio : from 0.67:1 (portrait) to 3:1 (panoramic) with any variation in between
- 11 color palettes : 8 for day time (2 by season), 3 for night time ("Quiet Moon", "Golden Moon", and "Blood Moon")

Press [S] to save as PNG

metadata.name: Teardrop
metadata.description:
I started this work as an introspection to my comprehension on the book of Wumen Guan (無門關), the gateless barrier. 

A question posed by zen master, Wumen Huikai (無門慧開), to whether there was a gate, at a given barrier, where one would wish to pass? There were, of course, infinite many ways to compose such a paradox. 

As I explored through different forms and composition, the gates had become either hearts and/or eyes looking upon us. The barrier (關 guan), a type of blockade of something, effectively became a perspective, (觀 guan), the watching over of some things with love.  

I realized, it was then trivial to debate whether and how such gates exist. And whether something in the sky was flying in and out of gates or non gates, is no more significant than if they were only the teardrops of someone, watching over us, cheering us on. The answer was a simple question of love. 

Press 1 to save png. Chrome only. Preview images are compressed.

metadata.description:
A generative cube city. 
Made in p5.js without webGL or any 3D library.
Arrange intensive cubes and strong colors to form interesting pictures.

Main variant is Type. 33% for a Upside Down city. 67% for a Normal.

Other variants:
2 patterns of Background (Stripe / Gradient)
2 patterns of Shadow (Homochromy / Contrast)
2 patterns of Cube Size (Large / Normal)
2 patterns of Stroke (Yes / No)
5 patterns of Fragment & 3 patterns of Stick Length.
And 24 selected Color Palettes.

Total 11,520 combinations.
All variants are selected and based on the balanced state between harmony and conflict.
